  ],
  "_false_agency_note": "Abstract/inanimate subject + a human cognition/volition verb. AI loves this because it avoids naming the actor ('the complaint becomes a fix' — someone fixed it). The fix is to name the human (or use 'you'), never to invent one. Conventional in academic/scientific prose ('the data show'), so the false_agency category is muted for the academic register.",
  "false_agency_patterns": [
    "\\bthe\\s+(data|market|markets|algorithm|model|system|process|metric|metrics|number|numbers|code|software|platform|product|feature|dashboard|report|spreadsheet)\\s+(tells?|knows?|wants?|decides?|believes?|thinks?|feels?|realizes?|realises?|understands?|chooses?|cares?|prefers?|rewards?|punishes?|demands?|insists?|expects?|remembers?|agrees?|hopes?)\\b",
    "\\bthe\\s+(complaint|decision|conversation|culture|narrative|momentum|consensus|truth|insight|realization|realisation)\\s+(emerges?|emerged|becomes?|became|shifts?|shifted|moves?|moved|takes\\s+hold|sets\\s+in|crystallizes?|crystallises?)\\b",
    "\\b(a|the)\\s+\\w+\\s+(lives?\\s+or\\s+dies?|lives\\s+and\\s+dies)\\b"
  ],
  "_negative_listing_note": "The multi-item negation striptease — listing what something is NOT across two or more sentences before revealing what it is. Distinct from the two-part 'not X, it's Y' (antithesis). State the final answer; the reader does not need the runway.",
  "negative_listing_patterns": [
    "\\b(it|this|that|he|she|they|we)\\s+(is|was|are|were)(?:n'?t|\\s+not)\\s+[^.?!\\n]{1,45}[.?!]\\s+(?:it|this|that|he|she|they|we)\\s+(?:is|was|are|were)(?:n'?t|\\s+not)\\b",
    "\\bnot\\s+(a|an|the|just|only|about)\\b[^.?!\\n]{1,40}[.?!]\\s+not\\s+(a|an|the|just|only|about)\\b"
  ],
  "_dramatic_fragmentation_note": "Sentence fragments deployed for manufactured profundity ('That's it. That's the tradeoff.', 'X. And Y. And Z.'). Performative simplicity reads as generated. Fragments are legitimate in creative/casual/release-notes prose, so this category is muted there via the 'fragments' register allowance.",
  "dramatic_fragmentation_patterns": [
    "\\bthat'?s it\\.\\s+that'?s (the|your|our|how|why|what)\\b",
    "\\.\\s+(and|or|but)\\s+\\w+\\.\\s+(and|or|but)\\s+\\w+\\.",
    "\\bthis (unlocks|changes|breaks|fixes) (something|everything)\\.\\s+\\w+\\."
  ],
